<header>
<div id="instruction">
	Look carefully at the charts and complete the reports by choosing the preposition which best fits each gap. The preposition should be both grammatically correct and correct according to the information shown in the charts.
	</div>
</header>

<section id="body">


<a id="clickme"><img class="imagetask" src="../media/btn_examtips.jpg" mode="1" id="1002"/></a>
<br/><br/><br/>

<div id="imgwrapper">
<p class="caption1"><b>Chart A</b></p>
<a id="visual1"><img class="dynamic" src="../media/MM_AW_005s.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/></a>

<p class="caption1"><b>Chart B</b></p>
<a id="visual2"><img class="dynamic" src="../media/MM_AW_006s.jpg" mode="1" id="1004"/></a>

<p class="caption1"><b>Chart C</b></p>
<a id="visual3"><img class="dynamic" src="../media/MM_AW_007s.jpg" mode="1" id="1004"/></a>
<p class="linespace"></p>
  </div>
      <div id="dropdown">
    <p>Chart A shows a general downward trend&#xA0; 
	<select id="q1">
	<option id="a1">over</option>
	<option id="a2">in</option>
	<option id="a3">until</option></select>
	&#xA0;the decade in the number of hours per week spent watching television. From just under 23.5 hours&#xA0; 
	<select id="q2">
	<option id="a4">on</option>
	<option id="a5">at</option>
	<option id="a6">in</option></select>
	&#xA0;1991, the number of viewing hours fell steadily&#xA0; 
	<select id="q3">
	<option id="a7">by</option>
	<option id="a8">until</option>
	<option id="a9">after</option></select>
	&#xA0;1995, when there was a marked rise.&#xA0; 
	<select id="q4">
	<option id="a10">Until</option>
	<option id="a11">From</option>
	<option id="a12">Between</option></select>
	&#xA0;1996 and 1998 there was another steady decline.&#xA0; 
	<select id="q5">
	<option id="a13">At</option>
	<option id="a14">In</option>
	<option id="a15">By</option></select> 
	&#xA0;1999 there was a sharp drop of nearly an hour. Time spent viewing continued to decline steadily&#xA0;
	<select id="q6">
	<option id="a16">over</option>
	<option id="a17">until</option>
	<option id="a18">after</option></select> 
	&#xA0;the rest of the period.</p>
	
  <p>Line graph B shows variations in audience size for Channel 1&#xA0;
  <select id="q7">
  <option id="a19">at</option>
  <option id="a20">in</option>
  <option id="a21">from</option></select> 
  &#xA0;different times&#xA0; 
  <select id="q8">
  <option id="a22">on</option>
  <option id="a23">in</option>
  <option id="a24">at</option></select>
  &#xA0;an average weekday. The first peak in audience figures comes&#xA0;
  <select id="q9">
  <option id="a25">to</option>
  <option id="a26">during</option>
  <option id="a27">at</option></select> 
  &#xA0;1 o'clock in the afternoon, when around 35 per cent of the population are watching. However, it is clear that prime time for Channel 1 is&#xA0; 
  <select id="q10">
  <option id="a28">to</option>
  <option id="a29">during</option>
  <option id="a30">at</option></select>
  &#xA0;the early evening.&#xA0; 
  <select id="q11">
  <option id="a31">At</option>
  <option id="a32">In</option>
  <option id="a33">During</option></select>
  &#xA0;6 p.m. well over 50 per cent of the population are tuned in and&#xA0; 
  <select id="q12">
  <option id="a34">to</option>
  <option id="a35">until</option>
  <option id="a36">from</option></select> 
  &#xA0;7 p.m.&#xA0; 
  <select id="q13">
  <option id="a37">to</option>
  <option id="a38">between</option>
  <option id="a39">at</option></select> 
  &#xA0;10 p.m. at least two-fifths of the population are watching. Not surprisingly, the percentage falls off dramatically&#xA0; 
  <select id="q14">
  <option id="a40">after</option>
  <option id="a41">during</option>
  <option id="a42">by</option></select> 
  &#xA0;midnight.&#xA0; 
  <select id="q15">
  <option id="a43">Until</option>
  <option id="a44">By</option>
  <option id="a45">During</option></select>
  &#xA0;3 a.m. only a tiny proportion of the population are watching and figure does not rise significantly&#xA0; 
  <select id="q16">
  <option id="a46">by</option>
  <option id="a47">to</option>
  <option id="a48">until</option></select>
  &#xA0;10 a.m. in the morning.</p>
  
  <p>Chart C shows trends in audience size for a popular soap opera&#xA0;
  <select id="q17">
  <option id="a49">from</option>
  <option id="a50">at</option>
  <option id="a51">over</option></select>
  &#xA0;a six-month period&#xA0; 
  <select id="q18">
  <option id="a52">at</option>
  <option id="a53">in</option>
  <option id="a54">on</option></select>
  &#xA0;2001. &#xA0;
  <select id="q19">
  <option id="a55">During</option>
  <option id="a56">Before</option>
  <option id="a57">In</option></select>
  &#xA0;the summer months, the programme attracted an audience of over 17 million.&#xA0;
  <select id="q20">
  <option id="a58">Between</option>
  <option id="a59">From</option>
  <option id="a60">In</option></select>
  &#xA0;June&#xA0; 
  <select id="q21">
  <option id="a61">during</option>
  <option id="a62">in</option>
  <option id="a63">to</option></select>
  &#xA0;August there was a marked decline in audience number but&#xA0; 
  <select id="q22">
  <option id="a64">at</option>
  <option id="a65">in</option>
  <option id="a66">by</option></select>
  &#xA0;September the figure had recovered to its original level.
  </p>
